OL,5,Ccell
OL,7,FTetteh Turkson, of the Crown
OL,8,FProsecution Service, said: "This was a
OL,9,Fshocking breach of the public's trust.
OL,10,FDe Sousa was clearly an enthusiastic
OL,11,Fparticipant who wrongly thought she
OL,12,Fwould avoid responsibility.
OL,14,F"The CPS recognises there is no excuse
OL,15,Ffor any prison officer who conducts
OL,16,Fthemselves in such a manner, and we
OL,17,Fwill never hesitate to prosecute those
OL,18,Fwho abuse their position of power.
